.docname {Dashboard}
.include {docs}

The Dashboard is your central hub for real-time monitoring. It opens to the **Table view**, a scannable overview of every monitored room in the selected building.

![The dashboard table view](../assets/figures/dashboard-table.svg)

*Figure 1 — The dashboard table view. Each row is a room; columns update live as sensors report.*

---

## The table view

Each row is one room in the current building, and each column is a property or live measurement. A newly registered building starts with the room name and capacity columns; you can add, remove, reorder, and save columns. See [Customizing the Data Table](building-table.qd) for the full guide.

---

## Occupancy status

CrowdVision derives an occupancy status from how full a room is relative to its capacity.

.var {headers}
   - Status
   - Occupancy

.tablebyrows {.headers}
    - - Empty
      - 0%
    - - Normal
      - 1% to 50%
    - - Crowded
      - 51% to 95%
    - - Full
      - 96% to 100%
    - - Overcrowded
      - over 100% — needs immediate attention

---

## Choosing a building

If you manage several buildings, switch between them from the selector at the top of the dashboard.

1. Open the **building selector** dropdown at the top of the view.
2. Pick a building you have access to.
3. The table refreshes instantly with that building's rooms and live data.

![The building selector dropdown](../assets/figures/building-selector.svg)

*Figure 2 — The building selector lists every building your account can access.*

---

## Switching views and Focus Mode

A toggle at the top of the dashboard switches between **List** (the table) and **Graph** (the charts — see [Charts & Simulator](sensors.qd)). A **Fullscreen** control expands the current view into a clean, distraction-free display for wall monitors.

![The List / Graph toggle and the Fullscreen control](../assets/figures/view-toggle.svg)

*Figure 3 — Switch between List and Graph, or enter Fullscreen (Focus Mode).*

- Click **Graph** to see visual analytics; click **List** to return to the table.
- Click **Fullscreen** to fill the screen; press `Esc` or click the control again to exit.
